SAY NAME1 ~Purging Touch~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC ~Purging Touch

The most trusted and worthy of Ilmater's followers are granted a powerful healing touch. Once per day, Sirene may heal one creature other than herself by half their total hit points and removing the effects of all poisons and diseases as well as the effects of blindness, deafness, fear, sleep, feeblemind, unconsciousness, and intoxication, as well as berserk and confused states of mind. In addition, the recipient is protected against spells and other attacks that cause these effects for 1 turn.~

COPY ~%MOD_FOLDER%/spells/C0sblind.spl~ ~override~
SAY NAME1 ~Racial Power: Blinding Gaze~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC ~Blinding Gaze

Sirene's racial powers allow her to blind others upon making eye contact. The target must make a saving throw vs. spells at -3 or become blinded for one turn. Additionally, targets have a 20% chance to go berserk for two rounds (no save).~

COPY ~%MOD_FOLDER%/spells/C0sburn.spl~ ~override~
SAY NAME1 ~Racial Power: Burning Hands~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC ~Burning Hands

Tieflings with infernal heritage have the innate power to cast the Burning Hands spell.

When Sirene casts this spell, a jet of searing flame shoots from her fingertips. Sirene's hands must be held so as to send forth a fan-like sheet of flames: her thumbs must touch each other and the fingers must be spread. The burning hands send out flame jets of 5 ft. length in a horizontal arc of about 120 degrees in front of Sirene. Any creature in the area of the flames suffers 1d3 points of damage, +2 points for each level of the caster, to a maximum of 1d3+20 points of fire damage. Those successfully saving vs. Spell receive half damage.~

COPY ~%MOD_FOLDER%/spells/C0sblur.spl~ ~override~
SAY NAME1 ~Racial Power: Blur~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC ~Blur

Tieflings with infernal heritage have the innate power to cast the Blur spell.

When a Blur spell is cast, Sirene causes the outline of her form to become blurred, shifting and wavering. This distortion causes all missile and melee attacks against her to be made with a -3 penalty. Sirene also gains a +1 bonus to all of her Saving Throws. The effects of this ability last for 4 rounds + 2 rounds per level.~

COPY ~%MOD_FOLDER%/spells/c0spr1.spl~ ~override~
SAY NAME1 ~Favor of Ilmater~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC ~Favor of Ilmater
(Necromancy)

Level: 3
Sphere: Necromantic, Protection
Range: 10 ft.
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: One creature
Duration: Instant
Saving Throw: None

This spell allows the priest to take on the injuries of another creature, healing 3 hit points per level of the caster and dealing the same amount to <PRO_HIMHER>self as non-lethal damage.~

COPY ~%MOD_FOLDER%/spells/c0spr2.spl~ ~override~
SAY NAME1 ~Endurance of Ilmater~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC ~Endurance of Ilmater
(Necromancy)

Level: 4
Sphere: Necromantic, Protection
Range: Touch
Casting Time: 7
Area of Effect: One creature
Duration: 1 round/level
Saving Throw: None

This spell doubles the hit points of the spell recipient for the spell duration. Any damage suffered is taken first from these phantom hit points until they are all exhausted; damage is only then taken from the real hit points of the affected being. The spell also protects the vitality of the spell recipient so that all system shock rolls and checks of any sort against contracting diseases automatically succeed, and all other saving throws receive a +2 bonus. In addition, no being protected by endurance of Ilmater can be knocked over, trampled, ridden down, or overthrown; all protected beings can stand firm against all charges.

Endurance of Ilmater may only affect the same target once every 8 hours - repeated castings will have no effect until that amount of time has passed.~

COPY ~%MOD_FOLDER%/spells/c0spr2a.spl~ ~override~
SAY NAME1 ~Endurance of Ilmater~

COPY ~%MOD_FOLDER%/spells/c0spr3.spl~ ~override~
SAY NAME1 ~Blast of Pain~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC ~Blast of Pain
(Evocation)

Level: 5
Sphere: Combat, Necromantic
Range: 10 ft.
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: One creature
Duration: 4 rounds
Saving Throw: Special

This spell creates a beam of smoky gray radiance that streaks unerringly from the priest to a single chosen target who must be within view and range of the caster as casting begins. The target creature must make a saving throw vs. spell at a -5 penalty. If the saving throw is successful, the target is overwhelmed by pain for one round (slowing its movement by half, adding 3 to all casting times, and forcing it to make all attack rolls at a -2 penalty) and suffers 1d4+1 points of non-lethal damage to its nervous system; it is then free of the spell.

If the saving throw is failed, the target creature suffers 4d6 points of non-lethal damage and is stunned and writhing helplessly in pain for the remainder of the current round and the following round. It can make no deliberate attacks, and its awareness of its surroundings is blotted out.

At the beginning of the second round after it was affected, the target being is allowed another saving throw vs. spell, this time at a -4 penalty. If the target succeeds at the saving throw, it suffers 1d4+1 points of non-lethal damage but is then free of the spell. If it fails, 3d6 points of non-lethal damage are inflicted, and the victim continues to be stunned and to writhe helplessly.

At the beginning of the third round after it was affected, the target is allowed a third saving throw vs. spell at a -3 penalty. If the saving throw is successful, the victim suffers 1d4+1 points of non-lethal damage and is then freed from the spell. If the saving throw is failed, 2d6 points of non-lethal damage are inflicted, and the victim continues to be stunned and to writhe helplessly until the end of the round, when the spell ends.~

